parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause poor visibility at night, making it difficult or impossible to drive safely, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: making it hard to see the road at night; low beam reflectors fail
causing up to 90% loss of candle power; plastic lenses on the front of the housings become foggy; light output with low beams is hardly more noticeable than driving with just parking lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: white smoke comes from the exhaust
and there is a sweet or antifreeze smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: and there is a sweet or antifreeze smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: and there is a grinding or whining noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems in the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The air ride control compressor fails
and there are electrical issues with the lights and wiring.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to bottom out, leading to loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
Electrical system failures can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Windows and trunk won't open or close
car won't turn off even when the key is removed
electrical issues with the air suspension system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunction of the McPherson struts can cause the vehicle to intermittently set up too high or drop to the ground, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle intermittently sets up too high or drops to the ground

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the stabilizer bar links can cause the vehicle to vibrate or wobble, leading to loss of control and accidents.
Misalignment can cause uneven tire wear, vibration, and loss of control, leading to accidents.
